{{Quote|I hope the Imps buy your story, Shug&mdash;I know I wouldn't.|Salla Zend to Shug Ninx, aboard the ''Salvager Three''|<ref name="DEII">''[[Star Wars: Dark Empire II]]''</ref>}}
'''''Salvager Three''''' was a freighter, bought by Shug Ninx, used as cover to enter [[Byss/Legends|Byss]] space by [[Salla Zend]] to retrieve her ship, the ''[[Starlight Intruder]]'' (they would later discover that it had been scrapped). ''Salvager Three'' was likely left behind by the pair on Byss after they decided to leave Byss with Ninx's ''[[Starhook Ten]]'' and a group of recently evacuated [[Alliance to Restore the Republic/Legends|Rebels]] or modified to ''become'' Starhook Ten.

{{Ship-stub}}

==Behind the scenes==
''Salvager Three'' could be another name for ''Starhook Ten'', given that both ships seem to be identical. Additionally, Ninx and Zend enter Byss with the former while using false codes and leave with the latter. However, a more likely explanation may be that Ninx had left the ''Starhook Ten'' at Byss prior to the events depicted in ''[[Star Wars: Dark Empire]]'' and ''[[Star Wars: Dark Empire II]]'' or that it was modified using what was left of the Starlight Intruder as the [[Star Wars Handbook 3: Dark Empire|Dark Empire Handbook]] would suggest.

''Salvager Three'' is misidentified as the '''''Starhook VII''''' in Ninx's entry in ''[[The Essential Guide to Characters]]''. This error is not present in Zend's entry.

